{"description":"Set up the build infrastructure for the marketing site redesign.

## Scope

### Modify
- `site/package.json` -- add: tailwindcss, @tailwindcss/vite, @fontsource/geist-sans, @fontsource/geist-mono, astro-icon, @iconify-json/ph
- `site/astro.config.mjs` -- add Tailwind as Vite plugin (NOT @astrojs/tailwind), configure astro-icon with include list for tree-shaking

### Create
- `site/src/styles/global.css` -- @import "tailwindcss" (NOT @tailwind directives), design tokens via @theme, scroll reveal CSS, spring easing variables, prefers-reduced-motion overrides, noscript visibility fallback

### Rewrite
- `site/src/layouts/Base.astro` -- new design system, Geist font imports via @fontsource, IntersectionObserver script (vanilla <script>, NOT client:visible), meta tags, OG tags, SoftwareApplication JSON-LD structured data

## Astro Config Pattern
```js
import { defineConfig } from 'astro/config';
import tailwindcss from '@tailwindcss/vite';
import icon from 'astro-icon';

export default defineConfig({
  site: 'https://lavra.dev',
  output: 'static',
  vite: { plugins: [tailwindcss()] },
  integrations: [
    icon({
      include: {
        ph: [/* only icons actually used */]
      }
    })
  ],
});
```

## global.css Pattern
```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --color-bg: #09090b;
  --color-surface: #18181b;
  --color-border: #27272a;
  --color-border-light: #3f3f46;
  --color-text: #fafafa;
  --color-text-muted: #a1a1aa;
  --color-text-dim: #71717a;
  --color-accent: #10b981;
  --color-accent-dim: #065f46;
  --color-danger: #ef4444;
  --color-amber: #f59e0b;

  --font-sans: "Geist Sans", sans-serif;
  --font-mono: "Geist Mono", monospace;

  --ease-spring: cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
  --ease-bounce: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);
}
```

## Animation System (research-corrected)
- Easing: --ease-spring: cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1) -- better for fade-up than original (0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)
- Stagger: Use inline --index custom property + calc(var(--index) * 80ms), NOT data-reveal-delay attributes (not cross-browser compatible with CSS calc)
- [data-reveal] elements start opacity:0 translateY(24px), gain .revealed class via IntersectionObserver
- Observer config: threshold 0, rootMargin "0px 0px -80px 0px", unobserve after first intersection
- Accessibility: ALL animation CSS inside @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) -- no-motion-first pattern
- Accessibility: Add <noscript><style>[data-reveal]{opacity:1;transform:none}</style></noscript> in Base.astro
- Accessibility: Check matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)') in JS -- if true, skip observer and instantly reveal all elements

## SEO (from research)
- OG image: 1200x630px, dark bg + command snippet + tool name
- JSON-LD: SoftwareApplication with applicationCategory: "DeveloperApplication", applicationSubCategory: "CommandLineApplication"
- Title format: "lavra -- Multi-agent workflow engine | lavra.dev"
- Canonical tag for lavra.dev (not www)

## Validation
- `cd site && bun install` succeeds
- `bun run build` succeeds with zero errors
- Base.astro renders with Geist font stack and zinc-950 bg
- Design tokens generate correct Tailwind utility classes (e.g., bg-bg, text-accent)
- IntersectionObserver fires correctly in vanilla <script>
- prefers-reduced-motion: elements visible without animation
- noscript: elements visible without JS"}

{"description":"Set up the build infrastructure for the marketing site redesign.

## Scope

### Modify
- site/package.json -- add: tailwindcss, @tailwindcss/vite, @fontsource/geist-sans, @fontsource/geist-mono, astro-icon, @iconify-json/ph
- site/astro.config.mjs -- add Tailwind as Vite plugin (NOT @astrojs/tailwind), configure astro-icon with include list

### Create
- site/src/styles/global.css -- @import "tailwindcss" (NOT @tailwind directives), design tokens via @theme, scroll reveal CSS, hero-gradient utility class, spring easing variable, prefers-reduced-motion overrides

### Rewrite
- site/src/layouts/Base.astro -- new design system, Geist font imports (weight-subset), font preload hints, IntersectionObserver script (vanilla <script>), CSP + security meta tags, JSON-LD structured data, OG tags. Include <Nav /> component import from start (do NOT include inline nav -- Nav component created in hm0.2).

## Astro Config Pattern
```js
import { defineConfig } from 'astro/config';
import tailwindcss from '@tailwindcss/vite';
import icon from 'astro-icon';

export default defineConfig({
  site: 'https://lavra.dev',
  output: 'static',
  vite: { plugins: [tailwindcss()] },
  integrations: [
    icon({ include: { ph: [/* only icons actually used */] } })
  ],
});
```

## global.css Pattern
```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --color-bg: #09090b;
  --color-surface: #18181b;
  --color-border: #27272a;
  --color-border-light: #3f3f46;
  --color-text: #fafafa;
  --color-text-muted: #a1a1aa;
  --color-text-dim: #71717a;
  --color-accent: #10b981;
  --color-accent-dim: #065f46;
  --font-sans: "Geist Sans", sans-serif;
  --font-mono: "Geist Mono", monospace;
  --ease-spring: cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
}

.hero-gradient {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #09090b 0%, #0c1a14 50%, #09090b 100%);
}
```
Note: --color-danger and --color-amber REMOVED (use Tailwind built-in red-500/amber-500 directly).
Note: --ease-bounce REMOVED (unused per simplicity review).
Note: hero-gradient defined as shared class (used by Hero, VideoDemo, InstallCta -- per architecture review).

## Font Loading (per performance review -- P0)
- Import ONLY needed weights:
  ```js
  import '@fontsource/geist-sans/400.css';
  import '@fontsource/geist-sans/700.css';
  import '@fontsource/geist-sans/900.css';
  import '@fontsource/geist-mono/400.css';
  import '@fontsource/geist-mono/700.css';
  ```
- Add <link rel="preload"> for Geist Sans 400 and 900 WOFF2 files in <head>
- After bun install, VERIFY actual font-family name in node_modules/@fontsource/geist-sans/index.css and update --font-sans accordingly
- font-display: swap (default) + preload minimizes swap window
- Use font-display: optional for Geist Mono (non-critical, eliminates FOUT)

## Animation System
- Single easing: --ease-spring: cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1)
- [data-reveal] elements start opacity:0 translateY(24px), gain .revealed class via observer
- Stagger: --index custom property + calc(var(--index) * N ms) -- ONLY on Pipeline cards
- Observer config: threshold 0, rootMargin "0px 0px -80px 0px", unobserve after first intersection
- CRITICAL: Do NOT put data-reveal on hero section (LCP must paint immediately)
- Accessibility: ALL animation inside @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)
- Accessibility: Check matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)') in JS -- skip observer, instantly reveal all
- Accessibility: <noscript><style>[data-reveal]{opacity:1;transform:none}</style></noscript>

## Security Meta Tags (per security review)
- CSP via meta http-equiv: default-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; frame-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'
- <meta http-equiv="X-Content-Type-Options" content="nosniff">
- <meta name="referrer" content="strict-origin-when-cross-origin">

## SEO
- JSON-LD: SoftwareApplication via JSON.stringify() (NOT template literal interpolation -- prevents script tag breakout)
- OG image: defer creation (noted in epic Deferred section)
- Title: "lavra -- Multi-agent workflow engine | lavra.dev"
- Canonical tag for lavra.dev

## Coordination with hm0.2 (per architecture review)
- Base.astro should import and render <Nav /> from the start
- hm0.1 creates Base.astro with <Nav /> placeholder import
- hm0.2 creates the actual Nav.astro component file
- This prevents Base.astro double-write

## Validation
- cd site && bun install succeeds
- bun run build succeeds with zero errors
- Verify font-family name matches @fontsource registration
- Base.astro renders with Geist font stack and zinc-950 bg
- Design tokens generate correct Tailwind utility classes
- hero-gradient class applies correct gradient
- IntersectionObserver fires in vanilla <script>
- CSP meta tag present in <head>
- prefers-reduced-motion: elements visible without animation
- noscript: elements visible without JS
- Ensure <script> tags are NOT is:inline (let Astro minify)"}

